IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: This incident was audibly and visually recorded using the Axon Digital Video Camera System installed in Maryland State Police Unit, U-16, as well as my Axon body worn camera. Narrative: On April 5, 2023, at approximately 0634 hours, I, TFC Moorman #6980, was on uniformed patrol operating unmarked Maryland State Police Vehicle, U-16. I responded to the area of Hallowing Point Road and JW Williams Road, Prince Frederick, Calvert County, Maryland for a reported injured deer in the roadway. I arrived and observed an injured deer lying in the middle of the westbound lane of Hallowing Point Road impeding traffic. I observed the deer had a broken rear leg and an unknown fluid was coming from its mouth. The deer attempted to stand multiple times but kept falling to the ground. The deer was suffering and unable to move. I retrieved my agency issued shotgun (Serial #V1390588). The deer had moved to the shoulder of the roadway and was lying in front of a large grass hill. The hill had no people, vehicles, or houses behind it. The sight picture was clear, and I incapacitated the deer to relieve its suffering. The deer was removed from the roadway. I used one agency issued slug shotgun round to incapacitate the deer. I returned to the Barrack and Sgt. Newman #3029 replaced the one slug shotgun round I used. Case closed. All events occurred in Calvert County, Maryland.
